# Harness parser conventions

## Registration checklist

1. Implement `find*Dirs()` + parse functions in `parser-<harness>.ts`
2. Register in `EXTERNAL_HARNESSES` (`parser-harnesses.ts`) with sync + optional async collector
3. Add harness name to `EXTERNAL_HARNESS_SET` (cache reconciliation)
4. Add UI color in `src/webview/shared.ts` if new harness label
5. Add trusted roots in `parser-shared.ts` when reading outside workspace
6. Add tests with temp dirs — no real user paths

## Cursor slug paths

Cursor encodes workspace paths as slugs (`c-Users-alice-myrepo`). `resolveCursorProjectPath` walks the filesystem when possible; tests must not assume a real path exists.

## OpenCode

Prefer SQLite (`opencode.db`) when present; fall back to JSON storage layout. Use shared row mappers in `parser-opencode.ts`.

## Dashboard gate

External harnesses run even when `findLogsDirs()` is empty. Use `hasExternalHarnessSources()` — do not reintroduce Copilot-only early exits in `panel.ts`.
